                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Ic/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-09T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1921—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>222. Your 279, August 5, 5 p.m.</p>
                <p>In view of your reports as to the urgency of the situation the Department
                    considers that action upon the suggestion contained in its 198, July 15, should
                    not be postponed to await the result of such an investigation. The Department
                    therefore hopes you will be able to obtain the early consent of the Diplomatic
                    Body thereto.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
